## .distignore — files excluded from the distributed plugin ZIP.
## Mirrors the `-x` exclude list in .github/workflows/update-release-latest.yml
## (the zip step is the actual gate; this file documents the contract and
## is what `wp dist-archive` / `svn` tooling would use).
##
## Plugin updates are handled by the WordPress.org plugin directory once
## the plugin is approved (no in-plugin updater is bundled). Before
## approval, operators install/update by uploading the GitHub release ZIP
## via WP Admin. The previous `update-checker.php` self-updater was
## removed in v1.47 because plugin-check (correctly) rejects in-plugin
## update mechanisms for WordPress.org submissions.

# Development tests (have CLI-only guards and phpcs:disable; not for end users).
tests/

# Developer-facing README (the user-facing copy is readme.txt).
README.md

# Editor / metadata noise.
.distignore
.editorconfig
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# OS noise.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Build / dev folders.
node_modules/
vendor/

# WordPress.org plugin screenshots — live in the SVN `assets/` folder
# alongside `trunk/` and `tags/`, NEVER inside the plugin zip itself.
# Kept in this folder during local editing for convenience; the zip step
# strips them out via the matching `zip -x` lines in
# `.github/workflows/update-release-latest.yml`. Glob covers any future
# additions (jpg/jpeg/gif are also valid per WP.org plugin assets docs).
screenshot-1.png
screenshot-2.png
screenshot-3.png
screenshot-*.png
screenshot-*.jpg
screenshot-*.jpeg
screenshot-*.gif

# Plugin banner + icon — also SVN `assets/` only, never in the zip.
banner-*.png
banner-*.jpg
icon-*.png
icon-*.jpg
